'''Tundan''' was the language spoken by the [[Sorcerers of Tund/Legends|Sorcerers of Tund]], a group of [[Sith (species)/Legends|Sith-blooded]] [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force users]] from the verdant [[Vergence/Legends|Force nexus]] of [[Tund/Legends|Tund]]. Though the origins of the Sorcerers could be traced to the [[Kissai]] [[Kissai heretics|outcasts]] who interpreted the death of [[Sith King]] [[Adas]] during the [[27,700 BBY]] [[invasion of Korriban]]<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> as a sign to reject the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]],<ref name="KOTORCGWE">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/KOTORweben5|text=KOTOR Campaign Guide Web Enhancement 5: Karnak Tetsu, Sorcerer of Tund}}</ref> Tundan was considered distinct from the [[Sith (language)|Sith language]] by the time of the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]].<ref name="TundanNote">Despite the Sith origins of the [[Sorcerers of Tund/Legends|Sorcerers of Tund]], the ''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]'' and [[Karnak Tetsu]]'s Web Enhancement entry list [[Kreia|Darth Traya]] and [[Karnak Tetsu]]&mdash;both of whom lived during the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]]&mdash;as fluent in both [[Sith (language)|Sith]] and Tundan, implying some degree of linguistic differentiation between the languages.</ref>

Known speakers of the Tundan language with some degree of fluency included the [[Sith (species)/Legends|Sith Offshoot]] [[Karnak Tetsu]],<ref name="KOTORCGWE" /> the [[Croke]] [[Rokur Gepta]],<ref name="DSS">''[[The Dark Side Sourcebook]]''</ref> and the [[Sith Triumvirate|Sith Triumvir]] [[Kreia|Darth Traya]].<ref name="KOTORCG">''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]''</ref> Additionally, a Tundan version of [[Asenec]]'s poem "[[The Gleam of Kiirium]]" was used as the source material for the [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Galactic Basic Standard]] translation produced by [[Kiekal Zzoh]].<ref name="SWEGTWAC">{{SW|url=news/the-essential-guide-to-warfare-authors-cut-part-3-xim-the-despot|series=Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Warfare Author's Cut|text=Part 3 - "Xim the Despot"}}</ref>

